<!DOCTYPE chapter SYSTEM "cruise_help.dtd">
<chapter title="Add a new stage to an existing pipeline">
    <p>Now that you have a pipeline with a single stage, lets add more stages to it.</p>
    <bullets>
        <item>Navigate to the new pipeline you created by clicking on the
            <strong>Edit</strong>
            link under the Actions against it. You can also click on the name of the pipeline.
        </item>
        <img src="resources/images/cruise/admin/add_stage/edit_pipeline_link.png"/>
        <item>Click on the Stages tab.</item>
        <img src="resources/images/cruise/admin/pipeline_general_options.png"/>
        <item>You will notice that a defaultStage exists. Click on the "Add new stage" link.</item>
        <img src="resources/images/cruise/admin/add_stage/stages_listing_with_add_stage_highlight.png"/>
        <item>Fill stage name and trigger type.</item>
        <item>Fill in the details for the first job and first task belonging to this job. You can <cref topic="admin_add_job">add more jobs </cref>and
            <cref topic="admin_add_task">add more tasks </cref>to the jobs.
        </item>
        <item>Click on help icon next to the fields to get additional details about the fields you are editing.</item>
        <img src="resources/images/cruise/admin/add_stage/add_stage_window.png"/>
        <item>Click "Save".</item>
    </bullets>
</chapter>
